@cactusplantfleamarket breaks all of streetwear's rules and only ends up better for it. In this industry, successful brands usually keep things simple, exclusive, and understated, quietly adding a few collaborations to their seasonal lineups. Not CPFM.â 
â 
On June 26, CPFM teased a collaboration with family-friendly animated flick @despicableme 4, comprising ultra-approachable logo wear. Earlier that week, models at @junyawatanabe's collaboration-heavy Spring/Summer 2025 menswear show clutched CPFM co-created accessories. These diverse partnerships showcase CPFM's unique ability to maintain cultural cachet while spanning both mass-market and high-fashion realms.â 
â 
Generally, streetwear brands fall into two categories: those frequently releasing mediocre merch with well-paying partners, and those whose rare collaborations become collector's items. CPFM defies this dichotomy, shifting seamlessly from McDonald's meals to Nike sneakers to one-off pop-ups without depleting its coveted clout.â 
â 
Founded by former @pharrell assistant Cynthia Lu in 2015, CPFM maintains a low profile despite its reach. It sparingly drops in-house creations via a bare-bones website and vacant Instagram page, letting partners and admirers handle promotion.â 
â 
Despicable Me is the first CPFM partnership that feels a little left-field.â 
But, again, CPFM bends the subject to its will. The cartoonish characters, kid-ish quirk, and goofy colors fit within the CPFM world.â 
â 
CPFM has clearly earned enough cultural capital to legitimize almost anything. What's next?â 
â

Caption:
"Aesthetics" and trends do not give you the right to shop from exploited labour âœ¨

When it comes to fashion designing, aesthetics comes 3rd when creating a garment. First is purpose, second is material. 

It is insane vanity to pin where we buy our clothes on aesthetics. If you really cared about ethical practices you wouldn't care about the aesthetic. 

I don't look aesthetic everyday. Most weeks I'll wear the same dress, and I won't even pair it with jewellery or accessories. I will just wear it because it serves its purpose, clothing me.

I hate the "I deserve trendy clothes" argument. No one deserves well curated aesthetics. But EVERYONE deserves fair working conditions and fair pay ğŸ¤Œ
